Cause: The rear sensor module is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the rear sensor module and replace if necessary.

Cause: The magnetic 3D circuit board for the lift sensor is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the magnetic 3D circuit board for the lift sensors and its cabling. Examine that the lift sensor magnets are not missing or installed in opposite direction. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The nose module or the main cable are damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine nose module or the main cable. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The LED status indicator on the product is damaged.
Action: Examine the display kit and the application circuit board and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The magnetic 3D circuit board for the collision sensor is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the magnetic 3D circuit board for the collision sensors and its cabling. Examine that the collision sensor magnets are not missing or installed in opposite direction. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The magnetic 3D circuit board for the collision sensor is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the magnetic 3D circuit board for the collision sensors and its cabling. Examine that the collision sensor magnets are not missing or installed in opposite direction. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The radar kit is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the radar kit and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The nose module or the main cable are damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine nose module or the main cable. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The EPOS Plug-in has been removed and you want to use the product with wire installation instead.
Action: Disable EPOS in the Automower® Connect app.

Cause: The EPOS Plug-in is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the EPOS Plug-in. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The temperature in the charging station is too high or too low for the product to operate.
Action: The product will continue with normal operation when the temperature in the charging station is within the set temperature limits. Make sure that the charging station is put in an area with protection from the sun.

Cause: The charging station circuit board is damaged.
Action: Examine the charging station circuit board. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The charging current is too high or too low. The power supply unit is damaged.
Action: Examine the power supply unit. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The charging voltage is too high or too low. The power supply unit is damaged.
Action: Examine the power supply unit. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The current in the N-field is too high or too low.
Action: Examine the antenna wire. Replace if necessary. If problem remains, examine the charging station circuit board. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The current in the F-field is too high or too low.
Action: Examine the antenna wire. Replace if necessary. If problem remains, examine the charging station circuit board. Replace if necessary.

Cause: Power failure
Action: Find and correct the cause of the power failure.

Cause: Only one of two wheel brush motors can be detected.
Action: Make sure that the wheel brush motors and their cables are installed correctly.  If the problem remains, speak to your authorized service center.

Cause: Only one of two wheel brush motors can be detected.
Action: Examine the drive unit motor control circuit board and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The rear loop circuit board is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the rear loop circuit board and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The main cutting system is blocked by grass or other objects.
Action: Examine the main cutting system and remove the grass or other objects.

Cause: The main cutting system or its cabling is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the main cutting system and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The battery state of health is low.
Action: Replace the battery.

Cause: The battery state of health is low.
Action: Replace the battery.

Cause: The battery is damaged.
Action: Replace the battery.

Cause: The charging station has been moved.
Action: Move the charging station to its original position or reinstall the charging station in the app to set its new position.

Cause: The reference station has been moved.
Action: Move the reference station to its original position or reinstall the reference station in the app to set its new position. If the reference station is moved to a new position, you have to make a factory reset and redo the installation with all maps.

Cause: There is a power problem with the accessory port.
Action: Switch off the product and disconnect and reconnect the accessory to the accessory port. Restart the product. If the problem stays, speak to your service center.

Cause: The hub circuit board is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the hub circuit board and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: If the error occurs as the same time as error 132 there is probably a problem with the EPOS plug-in.
Action: Examine the EPOS plug-in and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: If the error occurs at the same time as error 135 there is probably a problem with the radar kit.
Action: Examine the radar kit and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The temperature in the reference station is too high or too low for the product to operate.
Action: The product will continue with normal operation when the temperature in the reference station is within the set temperature limits.

Cause: The reference station circuit board is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the reference station circuit board and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The reference station is obscured and has bad satellite coverage.
Action: Make sure that the reference station is installed according the to instructions in a high and free position. If not, move the reference station to a better position. If the reference station is moved, you have to make a factory reset and redo the installation with all maps.

HMI Message: Reference station cannot detect satellite signals
Cause: The antenna is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the antenna and the reference station circuit board and their cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The lift sensor is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the accessory circuit board and its cabling. Examine that the lift sensor magnet is not missing or installed in opposite direction. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The motor control circuit board is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the motor control circuit board and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The edge cutting system is blocked by grass or other objects.
Action: Examine the edge cutting system and remove the grass or other objects.

Cause: The edge cutting system or its cabling is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the edge cutting system and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The motor control circuit board edge or its cabling is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the motor control circuit board edge and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The product has discovered vibrations in the edge cutting system
Action: Examine that the blades and screws are not damaged or worn. Make sure that all blades are correctly installed and that there is only one blade attached in each position on the blade disc.

Cause: The rear charging module is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the rear charging module and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The rear charging module is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the rear charging module and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The lift sensor is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the accessory circuit board and its cabling. Examine that the lift sensor magnet is not missing or installed in opposite direction. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The tilt sensor has incorrect values.
Action: Examine the application circuit board and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The boundary wire is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine that the boundary wire is connected correctly to the charging station. Examine all splices on the boundary wire. Examine if the boundary wire is damaged and repair it if it is necessary.

Cause: One or several cutting discs have been lost.
Action: Examine the cutting discs and reinstall the lost cutting disc. Make sure all cutting discs can rotate freely and are installed correctly.

Cause: The product sensed a collision in the EPOS™ module.
Action: Remove the object that the product collides with. If removal of the object is not possible, make a stay-out zone. For a boundary wire installation, make an island around the object.

Cause: The way of the destination is blocked by a stay-out zone.
Action: Edit or remove the stay-out zone or make a new installation of the work area.

Cause: There is no transport path to the work area.
Action: Make a transport path to the work area.

Cause: Technical problems with the EPOS™ via Husqvarna Cloud service.
Action: Wait and see if the problem it solved automatically. Restart the product. If the problem stays, speak to your authorized service center.

Cause: The product does not have cellular connection and cannot receive correction data.
Action: Make sure that you have cellular coverage in all parts of the area where the product operates.

Cause: The product does not have cellular or Wi-Fi connection and cannot receive correction data.
Action: Make sure that you have cellular or Wi-Fi coverage in all parts of the area where the product operates.

Cause: The battery state of health is low.
Action: Replace the battery

Cause: The wheel motor control circuit board is damaged.
Action: Examine the wheel motor control circuit board and replace if necessary.

Cause: The wheel motor control circuit board is damaged.
Action: Examine the wheel motor control circuit board and replace if necessary.

Cause: The cutting motor control circuit board is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the cutting motor control circuit board and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The cutting motor control circuit board is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the cutting motor control circuit board and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The cutting motor, the cutting motor control circuit board or its cabling is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the cutting motor, the cutting motor control circuit board and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The product will continue to operate, but with reduced speed.
Action: Clean the window for the radar. Restart the product. If the problem stays, speak to your approved servicing dealer.

Cause: The way back to the charging station is blocked by an obstacle.
Action: Remove the obstacle

Cause: The product cannot go into the charging station because it is blocked or the baseplate of the charging station is tilted or bent.
Action: Examine why the product cannot go into the charging station. Remove any objects and make sure that the baseplate of the charging station is not bent. Make sure that the ground where the charging station is placed and 1 m /3.3 ft in front of the charging station is level.

Cause: The cutting height adjustment cannot move its full range.
Action: Clean the underside of the product and the rubber bellows for the cutting height adjustment.

Cause: The product has been operating in demanding conditions, for example high temperature, too high or thick grass.
Action: The product will restart and continue to operate automatically once the temperature is ok again. If the problem comes back again the reason is most likely that the grass is too high or thick for being operated by the mower. If the mower does not restart automatically, speak to your authorized service center.

Cause: The product has been operating in demanding conditions, for example high temperature, too high or thick grass.
Action: The product will restart and continue to operate automatically once the temperature is ok again. If the problem comes back again the reason is most likely that the grass is too high or thick for being operated by the mower. If the mower does not restart automatically, speak to your authorized service center.

Cause: The wheel motor control circuit board is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the wheel motor control circuit board and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The wheel motor control circuit board is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the wheel motor control circuit board and its cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The product is not connected to the smart Gateway.
Action: Make sure that the smart Gateway is installed correctly, set to ON and connected to the Wi-Fi. If the problem occurs frequently when the product is at the same position, change the position of the smart Gateway to improve the connection signal between the product and and the smart Gateway.

Cause: The magnetic 3D circuit board for the lift sensor is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the magnetic 3D circuit board for the lift sensors and its cabling. Examine that the lift sensor magnets are not missing or installed in opposite direction. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The magnetic 3D circuit board for the rear collision sensor is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the magnetic 3D circuit board for the rear collision sensor and its cabling. Examine that the collision sensor magnet is not missing or installed in opposite direction. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The magnetic 3D circuit board for the front collision sensor is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the magnetic 3D circuit board for the front collision sensor and its cabling. Examine that the collision sensor magnet is not missing or installed in opposite direction. Replace if necessary.

Cause: One or several magnetic 3D circuit boards for the collision sensors are damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the magnetic 3D circuit boards for the collision sensors and their cabling. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The STOP button sensor is damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine that the STOP sensor magnet is not missing or installed in opposite direction. Examine the HMI circuit board and replace if necessary.

Cause: There is high charging power loss in the system.
Action: Examine the charging plates, the connector to the battery and all cabling in the product and the charging station. Use the Diagnostics tool to identify which component is damaged.

Cause: There is high internal power loss in the system.
Action: Examine the connectors and cables between the circuit boards in the product for any visible damages or issues. If no problems are found with the cables and connectors, use the Diagnostic tool to identify which component is damaged.

Cause: There is an internal voltage problem in the system.
Action: Use the Diagnostics tool to identify which component is damaged.

Cause: There is high internal temperature in the product.
Action: Use the Diagnostics tool in Autocheck to identify which component is damaged.

Cause: The body of the drive unit cannot move freely around its chassis.
Action: Examine that the body of the drive unit can move freely around its chassis. Examine that the body of the drive unit is correctly installed and there is no dirt blocking it. If the problem stays, speak to your authorized service center.

Cause: One or several magnetic 3D circuit boards for the rear collision sensors are damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the magnetic 3D circuit boards for the rear collision sensors in the drive unit and their cabling. Examine that the collision sensor magnets are not missing or installed in opposite direction. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The body of the cutting deck cannot move freely around its chassis.
Action: Examine that the body of the cutting deck can move freely around its chassis. Examine that the body of the cutting deck is correctly installed and there is no dirt blocking it. If the problem stays, speak to your authorized service center.

Cause: One or several magnetic 3D circuit boards for the front collision sensors are damaged or not installed correctly.
Action: Examine the magnetic 3D circuit boards for the front collision sensors in the cutting deck and their cabling. Examine that the collision sensor magnets are not missing or installed in opposite direction. Replace if necessary.

Cause: The contact between the charging plates on the product and the contact plates on the charging station is not good.
Action: Polish the charging plates and the contact plates on the charging station.
